Goals:
    - fast startup time
        - listen for chatter on the line at startup; if there isn't any after
          some time interval, then go to application
        - also check first byte of RRW to see if a valid application exists.
          if not, then stay in bootloader mode
    - set address in EEPROM
    - program new code
        - crc all code

Protocol:
    Fn  Args    Description
    ___ _______ ____________________________________________________
    N   0       NOP -- sent to wake bootloader up
    170 0       NOP -- alias for 'N' (send a lot of these to aid in clock recovery)
    A   1       Set 1-byte address of the device in EEPROM
    B   2       [High][Low] -- set divisor of the UART in EEPROM
    P   2       [Addr][Page...] - Send program one page at a time
    V   0       Verify -- If the code is bad, then write 0xFF to the first
                byte of the RRW so that the bootloader knows not to go to the
                application
